%h2{:id => 'movierok.do', :style=>'border-left: 1px solid white;padding: 20px;'} movierok.do
movierok.do is a 
%a{:href=> 'http://do.davebsd.com'}
  Gnome Do 
plugin the fast and simple way to start your movies. The plugin is a open source project developed by the movierok team.

%br
%br
#movierok_do_more{:style=> 'display:none'}
  %h3 Requirements
  To install and use movierk.do you need following requirements:
  %ul
    %li
      Linux with Gnome Do installed
    %li
      movierok.ff installed
  %br
  %br

  %h3 Installation
  Until movierok.do gets into the official plugin repository for Gnome Do you have to do it the 'old school' way:
  %ul
    %li
      download xul and dll
    %li
      put them into plugin folder
      %br (e.g. ~/.local/share/gnome-do/plugins or ~/.local/share/gnome-do/plugins-0.6.0)
    %li
      restart Gnome Do
  %br
  %br
  %h3 Usage
  %ul
    %li
      Configure the plugin
      %br
      =image_tag('clients/movierok_do_config.png')
      %br
      Set your movierok username and select your player. Now close the Configuration windows and wait some minutes (until downloading rip list and indexing is finished).
    %li
      Now start Gnome Do (e.g. super + space) and type a string until a rip is selected.
      =image_tag('clients/movierok_do_play.png')
    %li
      Here you can play the movie in your player or visit the rip page on movierok.org.
  %br
  %br
  %h3 Other
  For further information and source code visit
  %a{:href=> 'http://github.com/mordaroso/movierok.do'}
    movierok.do @ github.
  /.
